\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces 2D loss surfaces across three SHIDS tiers for Qwen3-0.6B-Base. (a)~Tier~1 (Random+TADN): isotropic basin, moderate loss range. (b)~Tier~2 (GradPCA+TADN): $5.2\times $ larger loss range, aligned with gradient variance. (c)~Tier~3 (Hessian+TADN): extreme curvature anisotropy (40.8:1) visible at curvature-aware scale ($\pm 0.025$). Each tier reveals qualitatively distinct geometric features. Contours show $\log _{10}(\text  {loss})$; red star marks $\theta ^*$.}}{7}{figure.caption.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:surfaces}{{3}{7}{2D loss surfaces across three SHIDS tiers for Qwen3-0.6B-Base. (a)~Tier~1 (Random+TADN): isotropic basin, moderate loss range. (b)~Tier~2 (GradPCA+TADN): $5.2\times $ larger loss range, aligned with gradient variance. (c)~Tier~3 (Hessian+TADN): extreme curvature anisotropy (40.8:1) visible at curvature-aware scale ($\pm 0.025$). Each tier reveals qualitatively distinct geometric features. Contours show $\log _{10}(\text {loss})$; red star marks $\theta ^*$}{figure.caption.5}{}}
